/* harmony default export */ __webpack_exports__["default"] = ("<app-hero heading=\"Hi! My name is Rohan\" img=\"introImage2.jpg\" subheading = \"\r\n\tI am a full stack developer who is always on the hunt for new challenges \r\n\tin the world of technology. Welcome to my website\">\r\n</app-hero>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"container\" id=\"my-story\">\r\n\t<section>\r\n\t\t<div class=\"page-header text-center my-story-header\">\r\n\t\t\t<h2>My Story<br><h5>The journey till now</h5></h2>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<hr>\r\n\t\t<app-image imgSrc=\"assets/images/ghy.png\" imgHref=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guwahati\" imgCaption=\"Guwahati\"></app-image>\r\n\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\tI was born in the city of Guwahati in India. It was back in 2001, when I first crossed paths with a personal computer.\r\n\t\t\tMy father bought these set of boxes that were connected by wires with a screen on one of them,\r\n\t\t\twhere you could draw with virtual paint and play games like solitaire and minesweeper. After using it for a few days,\r\n\t\t\tI no longer had to fight with my brother for the control of the television. I had found something else to dig \r\n\t\t\tmy head in. I soon got hold of a Britannica Encyclopedia CD, and played the quiz game over and over, so many times that I\r\n\t\t\tknew the answers even before reading the questions. Soon enough I got introduced to the programming language of Java as\r\n\t\t\tpart of the school curriculum and all I used to wonder is, how simple instructions that we were writing in Java could be\r\n\t\t\tactually used to create complex softwares that I used to run on my computer back home. At the time, it seemed improbable.\r\n\t\t</p>\r\n\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\tWith the increasing love of computers, I moved to Vellore to pursue Bachelors in Computer Science. Motivated with the zeal\r\n\t\t\tto learn about the craft of software making, I dug deeply into everything I learnt and gradutated with the degree of B.Tech\r\n\t\t\tin Computer Science.\r\n\t\t</p>\r\n\t\t<app-image imgSrc=\"assets/images/vit.png\" imgHref=\"https://www.vit.ac.in\" imgCaption=\"Vellore Institute of Technology\"></app-image>\r\n\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\tI had got placed into one of the biggest companies in travel technology and got the opportunity to undergo internship during\r\n\t\t\tlast semester of my college. During this period I simultanepusly worked on my final year project. My project guide had recently\r\n\t\t\tstarted working on initiatives in the smart city mission, which is a push by the Government of India to modernise cities across\r\n\t\t\tIndia. Hence, I decided to make a 'Smart Mirror' as my final year project. Here is video of the prototype that I made:\r\n\t\t</p>\r\n\t\t<app-youtube-video></app-youtube-video>\r\n\t\t<app-vertical-space></app-vertical-space>\r\n\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\tHope you enjoyed the video. Today, I am working as a software engineer at one of the companies which pioneered the global\r\n\t\t\tdistribution system(GDS). Incase you want to contact me please use the Contact Me page or just click on the contact me button\r\n\t\t\ton the top right of your screen. I will get back to you as soon as possible. Thanks for dropping bye. Adios!\r\n\t\t</p>\r\n\t</section>\r\n</div>\r\n\t");

